# ==============================================================================
# Reckons.AI — Safety Attestation Log  (append-only; generated, do not hand-edit)
# ==============================================================================
# A dated, recurring record that specific safety controls existed in the software
# and were VERIFIED to pass, from an early date onward. Generated by
# scripts/offline/safety-attestation.ts and committed, so git supplies what this
# record needs and we cannot otherwise buy: it is timestamped, ordered, and
# cryptographically chained — it cannot be backdated.
#
# This records what the SOFTWARE did. It records nothing about any user: the app
# has no server, no accounts, and no logs, and retains no user content.
#
# NOT a claim of enforcement. The controls are good-faith defaults in open-source,
# local-first, client-side code and are bypassable by design (COUNSEL-BRIEF.md §4).
# ==============================================================================

kb:attestation-2026-07-12-601cfec rdf:type ktype:SafetyAttestation ;
    rdfs:label        "Safety attestation 2026-07-12" ;
    kpred:attested-at "2026-07-12T16:54:14.124Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    kpred:git-commit  "601cfecd1c14340e595a78841aabf2bb9fd42bbd" ;
    kpred:controls-verified 5 ;
    kpred:controls-total    6 ;
    kpred:control     "ethics-preamble-present=PASS — An ETHICS_PREAMBLE refusing incitement, mass-casualty weapons instructions, sexualization of minors, and promotion of slavery/trafficking is defined in the codebase. [658 chars; 4/4 required prohibitions present]" ;
    kpred:control     "ethics-preamble-injected=PASS — Every code path that sends a system prompt to an LLM prepends the ETHICS_PREAMBLE. Verified by static analysis of the prompt sites, not by assertion. [5/5 prompt modules inject the preamble]" ;
    kpred:control     "preamble-no-drift=PASS — The MCP server carries a byte-identical copy of the preamble; the two cannot silently diverge. [identical (658 chars)]" ;
    kpred:control     "classifier-blocks-on-ingest=PASS — classifyText / classifyStatement rate content none|mature|blocked, and filterBlockedStatements removes blocked content during ingest. [4/4 classifier exports present]" ;
    kpred:control     "safety-tests-pass=PASS — The content-policy test suite is green as of this attestation. [28 tests passed]" ;
    kpred:control     "egress-model-enforced=FAIL — Every feature that DISTRIBUTES user data (Reckons.AI as intermediary) declares a safety gate and does not ship ahead of it; user-export paths carry no blocking gate (export is a right). Enforced by graph-lint. [urn:kbase:concept/graph-publishing: is 'in-progress' with mediated-distribution egress, but its gate kb:publish-safety-gate is only 'planned' — shipping ahead of its own safety gate. | urn:kbase:conce]" ;
    kpred:disclaimer  "Good-faith effort, not enforcement. Client-side, open-source, bypassable by design. Records software state only; no user data is retained." .

